docs.abstract: The country is moving beyond nuclear power. But at what cost?
docs.snippet: The country is moving beyond nuclear power. But at what cost?
docs.lead_paragraph: HAMBURG, Germany — Are the Germans irrational? Steven Pinker seems to think so. Professor Pinker, a Harvard psychologist, told the German newsmagazine Der Spiegel recently that if mankind wanted to stop climate change without stopping economic growth too, the world needed more nuclear energy, not less. Germany’s decision to step out of nuclear, he agreed, was “paranoid.”

headline.main: The Tragedy of Germany’s Energy Experiment

docs.abstract: He was important as a candidate even if we can’t see it now. Can he now help Elizabeth Warren build momentum?

docs.lead_paragraph: On Tuesday night Julián Castro appeared at a rally in Brooklyn alongside Elizabeth Warren to express support for her bid for the Democratic presidential nomination.
